cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on human action recognition using deep convolutional neural networks and RGB cameras, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method aims to reduce network complexity and improve performance, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experimental results involve video data, indicating a potential overlap with multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of neural networks suggests a possible connection to neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
